title: Neutron capture cross sections of curium isotopes measured with ANNRI at J-PARC

x4freetext: Neutron capture cross sections of curium isotopes
measured with ANNRI at J-PARC

x4freetext: Energy resolution of the pulsed neutron
ANNRI(BL04) beam line of MLF at J-PARC
Flight path length of 21.510 m.
Neutrons were produced by the spallation
reactions on a mercury target induced by a 3-GeV
proton beam. The proton beams were supplied at a
repetition rate of 25 Hz and under a proton beam
power of 293 kW with "single-bunch mode". Produced
neutrons were slowed down in a supercritical para
hydrogen moderator. The neutron beam was collimated
to a 7-mm diameter at the sample position.
Relative neutron flux was reconstructed using the 478
keV gamma-rays from gamma rays from 10B(n,alpha
gamma) 7Li reactions.
Array of Ge detector consists of two cluster-
Ge detectors and eight coaxial-Ge detectors with BGO
anti-coincidence shields.
DAQ: CAEN V1724 Digitizer (14bit, 100MHz)
The 244Cm sample and the 246Cm sample were used. The
244Cm sample and the 246Cm sample contained curium
oxide with weight of 0.6 and 2.1 mg.
The isotopic and chemical impurities (mol%):
244Cm sample          246Cm sample
Each sample was sealed in an aluminum case with an
outer diameter of 9 mm and a wall thickness of 0.5 mm.
For the calibration of the time-to-energy conversion
function, a thin 197Au sample was used.
Dead Time Correction was applied with a paralyzable
dead time model.
Correction factors for self shielding and multiple
scattering were deduced using the Monte-Carlo
simulation code PHITS.
The influence of fission events was estimated from the
yield of an isolated peak of 247Cm resonance
at 3.175 eV with the 246Cm sample.
The neutron energy was calibrated by measuring a Au
sample with well-known neutron resonances.
Measurements with the carbon sample,
"Dummy replica sample", and "Blank (no sample) " were
used for back ground estimation.
Detection efficiency of capture gamma-rays for each
resonance was assumed to be constant.
The neutron capture cross sections were normalized
using the peak area of the first resonance of 240Pu.

x4freetext: Resonance energies, neutron and gamma widths were
determined with REFIT using Reich-Moor approximation.
- The spectra for the 244Cm and 246Cm samples were
fitted simultaneously.
- The ANNRI beamline resolution function was taken
from the work of Kino. See REL-REF.
- Additional uncertainty of 2.5% was assumed to
every data point as the uncertainty of the
response functions.
- The ideal gas model implemented in REFIT with
a sample temperature of 293 K was adopted for
the Doppler broadening.
- The initial delay and flight path were derived
using the results from the Au sample measurement.
